        <mxCell id="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-2" edge="1" parent="1" source="bwjHSVQv5VCAhcKKyRjm-4" style="endArrow=openThin;html=1;rounded=0;endFill=0;strokeColor=light-dark(#929090, #ededed);exitX=0.25;exitY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=1;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" target="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-1" value="">
          <mxGeometry height="50" relative="1" width="50" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="-120" y="230" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="-70" y="180" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-3" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;fontFamily=Comic Sans MS;" value="&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Failure &amp;amp; Consistency&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;- A network partition splits the cluster into a 2-AZ side and a 1-AZ side. What happens to a write with &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;W=2&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;? How does the behavior change when &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;sloppy quorum&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; is enabled, and in what way does sloppy quorum weaken the guarantee that &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;R + W &amp;gt; N&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; will always return the latest version&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;- A client reads an object and then writes it back using an &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;outdated context/version&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;. How does the system detect this situation, and how is the conflict handled?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;- Why does a delete operation require a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;tombstone&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; instead of immediately removing the data? What can happen if tombstones are garbage-collected too early (i.e., the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;resurrected key&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; problem)?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="220" width="410" x="-150" y="-120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-4" edge="1" parent="1" source="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-1" style="endArrow=openThin;html=1;rounded=0;endFill=0;strokeColor=light-dark(#929090, #ededed);exitX=0.5;exitY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.75;entryY=1;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" target="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-3" value="">
          <mxGeometry height="50" relative="1" width="50" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="-50" y="370" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint y="320" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-5" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;fontFamily=Comic Sans MS;" value="&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Hot Keys &amp;amp; Cluster Scaling&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;A flash-sale key suddenly accounts for &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;5% of total traffic&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; and is concentrated on only &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;N=3 nodes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;. How would you mitigate the hotspot? Discuss techniques such as &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;request coalescing&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;multi-layer caching&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;key salting/sharding for counter-style workloads&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, temporary &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;replication-factor expansion&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, and other approaches&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;- You add &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;30 new nodes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; to an existing &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;300-node cluster&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;. How is data rebalanced and transferred to the new nodes? How would you &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;throttle rebalancing traffic&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; to avoid violating service-level objectives (SLOs)? How are &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;reads and writes handled during data migration&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; to ensure availability and consistency?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="180" width="490" x="-690" y="-20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-6" edge="1" parent="1" source="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-1" style="endArrow=openThin;html=1;rounded=0;endFill=0;strokeColor=light-dark(#929090, #ededed);exitX=0.25;exitY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=1;entryY=0.75;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" target="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-5" value="">
          <mxGeometry height="50" relative="1" width="50" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="-280" y="40" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="-230" y="-10" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aUNtAYhIRR93k3x2W3pg-7" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;fontFamily=Comic Sans MS;" value="&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Design &amp;amp; Trade-offs&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;In what situations would you choose a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;CP system&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; (e.g., &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;etcd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; or a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Google Spanner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;-style architecture) instead of a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Dynamo-style AP system&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;? Provide concrete use cases and explain the trade-offs involved.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;- If the product requires &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;read-your-writes consistency&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; within a user session, what changes would you make? Discuss options such as &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;session stickiness&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;client-side version/context tracking&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;leader reads&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;R/W quorum tuning&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, or other techniques.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;- How would the design evolve when expanding to a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;multi-region active-active&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; deployment? How does the frequency of write conflicts change, and would you need a different conflict-resolution strategy (e.g., vector clocks, CRDTs, application-level merge logic, or stronger consistency guarantees)?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="230" width="520" x="320" y="-120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
